{
  "texts": [
    "The event's location and time, the people, objects, actions, thoughts, and perceptual details involved are all internal details.",
    "External details, on the other hand, are largely non-episodic details.",
    "These are any details that do not belong in the internal details category, and mainly consist of factual information that does not require the participant to remember or imagine a specific event (e.g., \"I've always enjoyed going to the beach for my birthday\").",
    "Participants sometimes provide information about events other than the central event they are being asked to describe.",
    "These details, while episodic in nature, are considered external details as well."
  ]
}